#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml[lang]:3-1
msgid "en"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.head.title:12-1
msgid "Window List dialog"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgid "Window List Dialog Box"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"This topic documents the settings available in the Window List dialog box "
"(also known as the JAWS Task List). This dialog allows you to switch between "
"running applications. To access this dialog, press <b>INSERT+F10</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:19-1
msgid "Running Applications"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:20-1
msgid ""
"This list box lists the running applications that are displayed on the task "
"bar. The window state of each application is also listed. The window state "
"will be minimized, restored, or maximized. You can select an application "
"from the list and press <b>ENTER</b> to switch to that application. Press "
"<b>DELETE</b> on an application to close it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:21-1
msgid "Only Include On Top Windows"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:22-1
msgid ""
"Select this check box to make it easier to interact with topmost windows, "
"often referred to as On Top windows. These are application windows that pop "
"up, without gaining focus or being in the <strong>ALT+TAB</strong> order. "
"These are often found with firewall or antivirus programs and are intended "
"to interrupt and provide information that must be acted on before "
"continuing. You cannot minimize them or press <strong>ALT+TAB</strong> to "
"move focus to another application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:23-1
msgid ""
"When this check box is selected, the On Top windows are included in the JAWS "
"Task List so that you can check to see if one of these windows is present. "
"If it is, you can switch focus to the window from the Window List dialog box "
"using the Switch To button. You can quickly identify On Top windows in the "
"Window List because they include the term \"On Top\" in the name."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:24-1
msgid "Switch To"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"This button allows you to switch to the application selected in the Running "
"Applications list box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:26-1
msgid "Cancel"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
msgid ""
"This button allows you to exit the Window List dialog box without switching "
"to a different application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:28-1
msgid "About"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cwindow_list_dialog.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:29-1
msgid ""
"This button allows you to view a dialog containing copyright information for "
"the Window List dialog box."
msgstr ""

